page.title: 02Wildlife
page.content: Where I live there is a lot of woodland and I see lots of wildlife.At night when it's starting to get you can see badgers seeking food.Later you hear the dustbins go over.If you look out you will see the badgers in the bins.We used to have some chickens but the foxes came and killed them.We see a lot of hares in spring having boxing matches.We see most animals in summer.There's a squirrel's drey near the oldest tree and when there are apples the squirrels come and pinch them.In the winter time you can see the mice digging tunnels in the snow.Sometimes the owls dive and get the mice.We have lots of birds nesting in the old walls and there are some swallows nesting in the stable.
